    "Though most papers examined the effects on various aspects of water access, the split across water, sanitation and hygiene was marginal.",
    "This demonstrates the recognition that, holistically, water, sanitation, and hygiene services and behaviours contribute to maintaining public health during weather events.Although the impacts on women and girls were present in over half the studies, evidence related to people with disabilities remains scarce.",
    "This pattern is observed in studies that assessed disability inclusion in WASH-related policies in Nepal, Bangladesh, and Cambodia compared to gender [61,62].",
    "Across all countries, attention to disability was considerably less than to gender.",
    "Both populations are vulnerable to the risks of climate change, so studies relating to these populations must be equally increased."
